				<span class="postdetails">
					<br /><b>Joined:</b> Wed Nov 10, 2004 6:47 pm<br /><b>Posts:</b> 1694
				</span>

			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">lidnariq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">There's a comment in the Nestopia source-<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">// looks like there's some protection from rapid writes on register<br />// reset, otherwise games like 'AD&amp;D Hillsfar' and 'Bill &amp; Ted' will break<br /><br />NST_DEBUG_MSG("MMC1 PRG write ignored!");<br /></div><br /><br />Maybe this is what you're triggering?</div>
<br />
<br />
<br />Those rapid writes are triggered by RMW instructions like INC (which have writes on two consecutive cycles).
<br />
<br />AFAIK, two side-by-side STAs are perfectly fine (in fact many commercial games do that without problems).  It's just if you do something like 'INC $FFFF' that you'll have that problem.</div>

