			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">dr00id88 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I checked that INC $FFFF to reset before, but it works properly only at FCEU.</div><br /><br />Do not do INC $FFFF (or any other RMW instruction) to write to registers.  It's a sloppy and unnecessary shortcut that would probably end up being problematic.  Use STA/STX/STY to write to registers... always.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Do I have to reset mapper every time I want to write to it?</div><br /><br />No.. just do it once at startup.  As long as you keep your writes in sets of 5s, you should never have to reset it during the program.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">If I don't reset that mapper, when I want to change the CHR page the second time (the next time...) it load different page that I wanted.</div>
<br />
<br />You shouldn't be having this kind of problem.  Either you're selecting the wrong page, the page you want isn't the one you think it is, or you're doing something wrong in how you're swapping it.  I can't say what the problem is without seeing the program.
<br />
<br />For certain, though, you don't need to reset before every write (and in fact, you shouldn't, as resetting will change modes and stuff on you, which you might not want).</div>

